The Reserve Bank is about to announce a decision on interest rates. Its already cut the repo rate by 3 percentage points since the start of the year. JOHANNESBURG - Will the South African Reserve Bank further reduce the interest rate when it makes its decision on Thursday afternoon? Some economists expect a further rate cut after the economy's terrible performance in the second quarter. READ: SARB cuts interest rate by 25 basis points The lower inflation outlook also supports the case for interest rate cuts. Consumers have so far received rate cuts of 300 basis points this year as the Reserve Bank tries to cushion the impact of COVID-19.